SECTION 1: THE FULL M8E SCALING EQUATION
--------------------------------------------------

  The scaling equation is a three-part causal chain:

  PART 1 -- n-Layer Topology (4D Euler Characteristic):

    V(n) - E(n) + F(n) - C(n) = 0

    where C(n) = n = cell count = layer count of the projected 4-polytope.
    This is the 4D generalization of Euler's polyhedron formula.
    For every convex 4-polytope: V - E + F - C = 0 (chi = 0 on S^3).

  PART 2 -- H3/H4 Symmetry Bridge (Rogers 4350B substrate):

    H3/H4 theta(n): Coxeter angle structure {60, 108, 144} deg (H3)
                    maps to {60, 90, 108, 144} deg (H4) via layer scaling.
    Rogers 4350B enforces: Dk=3.48, Df=0.0037 at 10 GHz.
    The M8C Coxeter gear ratio (h_H4/h_H3)^{1/4} = 3^{1/4} cancels
    the BC normalization ratio (h_H3/h_H4)^{1/4} exactly.

  PART 3 -- M* Scaling (Bost-Connes, time ratio form):

    t_cav(n) / t_vac  =  1 / (k_c^(120) * (n/120)^{1/4})

  Combined (THEOREM 1):

    k_c(n) = k_c^(120) * (n / 120)^{1/4}  where n = C (cell count)

