SECTION 4: DERIVATION OF THE 1/4 EXPONENT
--------------------------------------------------

  Four steps from topology to M* scaling:

  Step 1 -- 4D Volume:   V_{4D} ~ R^4  (120-cell in R^4)
  Step 2 -- 3D Proj:     sigma ~ R^3   (PCB coupling, layer-stack z lost)
  Step 3 -- Energy:      u ~ E^2  =>  E ~ R^{3/2}
  Step 4 -- BC Norm:     M* ~ h^{-1}   (Coxeter number h)

  Raw formula:   k_c ~ (h_H3/h_H4)^{1/4} * (n/120)^{1/4}

  Coxeter ratio (h_H3/h_H4)^{1/4} = 0.75983569
  Gear factor   (h_H4/h_H3)^{1/4} = 1.316074  (from M8C)
  Product                           = 1.0  (= 1 exactly)

  THEOREM 1 (Coxeter factors cancel; only cell count survives):

    k_c(n)  =  k_c(H4)  x  ( n / 120 )^{1/4}

  Equivalently (time ratio form, Part 3 of full equation):

    t_cav(n) / t_vac  =  1 / (k_c(H4) * (n/120)^{1/4})

