SECTION 7: PHI COINCIDENCE AND GEAR CANCELLATION
--------------------------------------------------

  Intermediate product (before gear factor):
    3.183 x (10/30)^{1/4} x (24/120)^{1/4}
    = 3.183 x 0.75983569 x 0.6687403
    = 1.6173865
    phi = 1.618034
    |diff| = 0.000647  (< 0.001 -- near-coincidence)

  The H4 polytope family has icosahedral (phi) symmetry at its root:
  The 120-cell has 120 dodecahedral cells, each face a regular pentagon.
  The golden ratio phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 governs both H3 (icosahedron)
  and H4 (120-cell). The phi near-coincidence is structural, not accidental.

